tafsir[12]{c,v,t}:
  75,21,"and leave be the Hereafter."
  75,23,"gazing upon their Lord;"
  75,25,"thou mightest think the Calamity has been wreaked on them."
  75,26,"No indeed; when it reaches the clavicles"
  75,28,"and he thinks that it is the parting"
  75,30,"upon that day unto thy Lord shall be the driving."
  75,33,"then he went to his household arrogantly."
  75,34,"Nearer to thee and nearer"
  75,35,"then nearer to thee and nearer!"
  75,37,"Was he not a sperm-drop spilled?"
  76,1,"Has there come on man a while of time when he was a thing unremembered?"
  76,3,"Surely We guided him upon the way whether he be thankful or unthankful."